rComments: Wonderful teacher to have for my first quarter! Always positive, always helpful and gives constructive advice. Strict on attendence, but made our Tuesday-Thursday class just a tuesday class, with Thursday being office hours.

Why are all the writing teachers in SC good?! I wish i could say the same for ECON... Tiffany was extremely helpful, nice and gave constructive criticism. I recommend her to anybody taking Writin 2. Just participate in class and show effort, you will EARN your A!

Tiffany was awesome. I highly recommend her because she like no other writing 2 teacher. She is funny and really has a laid back class. The essay was fairly easy and she would give us time in class to peer edit it. I love this teacher.

The overall class was interesting. However she didn't actually "grade" your essays. Hardly any feedback. Extremely strict when it comes to attendance and tardiness. Don't bother emailing her essays if you don't show up to class (which is mandatory) she won't check them/or say she didn't get it. Hard A. Don't get on her bad side; she's very biased.

coolest professor ever! she present the theme "asian diaspora" very well.unlike most professors, she dont judge you by how well you write but rather focus on the style you write. she believe that everyone has their own personality when they write, therefore she really encourage you to develop your own voice in writing.she is just awesome and fun!
Very fun teacher! She shows many videos in class and loves when students volunteer and get involved. Very open class with broad topics. Easy to get an A if you show up and put in some effort.
by the far the best english teacher out there. I recommend her 100% she is very strict with attendance and doesnt like people being late. As long as you show up for class and give some effort EASY A

i had tiffany for writing 2 'Asian Diaspora' and she is by far the most reasonable, creative, chill professor at Santa Cruz.she helped my writing skills mature and grow beyond the contemporary style of writing we're very used to in a college setting. i was never bored in her class.
